I was helping a nice level 7ish Elven lass recover her corpse some time ago with my previous FV character, a 27th level Ranger.  I camoflaged both of us, and we found her corpse.  While she was looting it, *I* was hit by Equestrielle *once*, even though I was camoed; the Elven person was not hit.  Rather than run screaming for the zone, my chivalrous nature prevailed and I waited for her to finish looting her corpse, saying something to her like &quot;Hurry please, I am in trouble here&quot;, or words to that effect.  Equestrielle did not attack either of us again.  I camoed us both and we left the zone.  But wait, there's more...<br>
<br>
Later that evening, I asked the Elven person to help me collect microservers ( since they were then affected by the TLC).  Once again, I camoed us and we started the run through LFay.  Near the zone, her camo broke and she was immediately hit by the horse for 401 damage, and died instantly.  Equestrielle then proceeded to attack me, while I was still camoed.  Rather than try to fight I ran for the zone, even though she cast fearsome spells on me, causing me to stagger about like a drunken chicken.  I finally made the zone with about 10hp left.  Why she didn't kill me I don't know; I would have been an easy kill.<br>
<br>
Perhaps she is programmed to attack randomly with a certain probability.  Or maybe she hates PCs in groups;  I have been through LFay many times camoed or invised alone and run right by her with no problem.<br>
<br>
